            <p class="lead">Insurance is the part of Airbnb hosting that nobody wants to think about until something goes wrong. A guest slips on your front steps. A pipe bursts while you're away. A visitor's child pulls a TV off the wall. Without the right coverage, any of these scenarios could cost you tens of thousands of dollars.</p>
